{
  "texts": [
    "Davidson nonetheless insists that this is how the action should be understood.",
    "He answers 'yes' to his own question.Davidson's answer requires us to factorise the complex interaction between the agent's body and the laces into agential and non-agential components.",
    "This done, the next move is to understand the non-agential component -the movement of the laces -as instrumentally related to the intention behind the basic actions involved in moving one's body so as to tie the laces.",
    "These movements are the means by which an intention to tie one's shoes gets realised, but both this intention and the bodily movements are separable from those of the laces themselves.",
    "Maybe one can only make the finger movements with the laces in hand -although, of course, doing so without the laces is \"a trick one might learn\" (ibid.)."
  ]
}